title._content: Sun breaking through thunder clouds - Madurai

description._content: At evening dusk a view on the Vaigai River passing the center of Madurai city by stormy weather. They had to release the water from the Vaigai Dam, you can imagine, all the sticks are there to hang up the laundry but now the river was flooded with water. Date Taken: 2006-03-03 Canon EOS 5D, 24-70mm f/2.8L, RAW, ISO-1600 Exposure: f/6.3, 1/60 seconds oochappan ©®

I was waiting for a train to pass, so reluctant to swap lenses for a shot at the birds, thinking 300mm may not have enough reach for the birds anyway.
